theorem Topology.P3_union_left_of_dense
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hDense : Dense (A : Set X)) : Topology.P3 (A ∪ B) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hx
  -- `closure A` is the whole space.
  have h_closureA : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := hDense.closure_eq
  -- Therefore, `closure (A ∪ B)` is also the whole space.
  have h_closure_union : closure (A ∪ B : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    -- One inclusion is obvious.
    have h_subset_univ : closure (A ∪ B : Set X) ⊆ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
      intro y hy; simp
    -- For the other inclusion, note that `closure A ⊆ closure (A ∪ B)`.
    have h_univ_subset : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure (A ∪ B : Set X) := by
      intro y hy
      have hy_closureA : (y : X) ∈ closure A := by
        -- Using `closure A = univ`.
        simpa [h_closureA] using (by
          have : (y : X) ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
            simp
          exact this)
      -- Monotonicity of `closure`.
      have h_incl : closure A ⊆ closure (A ∪ B) := by
        apply closure_mono
        intro z hz; exact Or.inl hz
      exact h_incl hy_closureA
    exact Set.Subset.antisymm h_subset_univ h_univ_subset
  -- Consequently, the interior is also the whole space.
  have h_interior : interior (closure (A ∪ B : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa [h_closure_union, interior_univ]
  -- Finish the proof.
  have : (x : X) ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simp
  simpa [h_interior] using this

theorem Topology.interiorClosureClosure_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (closure A)) = interior (closure A) := by
  simpa [closure_closure]
